ments\", \"from\": 344, \"to\": 368}, {\"ngram\": \"both June\", \"from\": 372, \"to\": 381}, {\"ngram\": \"July\", \"from\": 386, \"to\": 390}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It coincided with Ireland's\\\"very successful\\\" Olympic Games earlier in the month which as the report notes did not produce \\\"a pronounced feel-good factor\\\".\", \"from\": 393, \"to\": 547, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Ireland's\\\"very successful\\\" Olympic Games\", \"from\": 411, \"to\": 451}, {\"ngram\": \"the month\", \"from\": 463, \"to\": 472}, {\"ngram\": \"the report notes\", \"from\": 482, \"to\": 498}, {\"ngram\": \"a pronounced feel-good factor\", \"from\": 516, \"to\": 545}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"In the context of the old Roman adage, it seems that Irish consumers are much more concerned with bread than with circuses,\\\" said author Austin Hughes.\", \"from\": 549, \"to\": 701, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 576, \"end\": 581, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roman_Empire\", \"score\": 0.6715596597362078, \"rank\": 0.4878296629446753, \"text\": \"Roman\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roman_Empire\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roman_Empire\"}, {\"begin\": 603, \"end\": 608, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.7305995983581774, \"rank\": 0.3563641668402798, \"text\": \"Irish\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}, {\"begin\": 687, \"end\": 693, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Austin_Motor_Company\", \"score\": 0.9978354080227996, \"rank\": 0.0015515750402072428, \"text\": \"Austin\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Austin_Motor_Company\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Austin_Motor_Company\"}, {\"begin\": 694, \"end\": 700, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Howar